`crates/uv-auth/src/lib.rs` is the library entry point of the `uv-auth`
crate. It contains no logic of its own — it only declares the crate's
sibling modules as private (`mod ...`) and re-exports their public API
at the crate root (`pub use ...`).

```rust
// from crates/uv-auth/src/lib.rs
pub use access_token::AccessToken;
pub use cache::CredentialsCache;
pub use credentials::{Credentials, Username};
pub use index::{AuthPolicy, Index, Indexes};
pub use keyring::KeyringProvider;
pub use middleware::AuthMiddleware;
pub use pyx::{
    DEFAULT_TOLERANCE_SECS, PyxJwt, PyxOAuthTokens, PyxTokenStore, PyxTokens, TokenStoreError,
    is_default_pyx_domain,
};
pub use realm::{Realm, RealmRef};
pub use service::{Service, ServiceParseError};
pub use store::{AuthBackend, AuthScheme, TextCredentialStore, TomlCredentialError};

mod access_token;
mod cache;
mod credentials;
mod index;
mod keyring;
mod middleware;
mod providers;
mod pyx;
mod realm;
mod service;
mod store;
```

Reading this single file gives a complete inventory of the crate's
public surface and its internal module layout in one shot:

- Credential types: `Credentials`, `Username`, `CredentialsCache`,
  `AccessToken`.
- Storage backends: `TextCredentialStore`, `AuthBackend`, `AuthScheme`,
  `TomlCredentialError`, plus the OS `KeyringProvider`.
- HTTP integration: `AuthMiddleware`, `Service`, `Realm`, `RealmRef`,
  `Index`, `Indexes`, `AuthPolicy`.
- Pyx-specific OAuth token store: `PyxTokenStore`, `PyxJwt`,
  `PyxOAuthTokens`, `PyxTokens`, `TokenStoreError`,
  `DEFAULT_TOLERANCE_SECS`, `is_default_pyx_domain`.

The internal module `providers` is the only sibling module not
re-exported here, so it is crate-private wiring rather than part of the
external API.
